{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"bovid-ambient-bactrian","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Description\nImplement the LOC + size adapter behind the analyzer interface by shelling out to `scc --format json` (deterministic, no network). Populates AnalyzerResult.loc (per-file/per-language line counts + max). Absent scc binary -> Unavailable (honest), never fabricated zeros.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Adapter shells to scc over the configured scan root, parses JSON, returns per-file/per-language LOC + max_loc.\n- [ ] scc not on PATH / non-zero exit -> Unavailable(\"scc not available\"), not a crash and not zeros.\n- [ ] Deterministic: same tree -> same result; no network, no LLM.\n- [ ] Registered for multiple languages (language-agnostic).\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Unit tests with a monkeypatched `run_scc` seam (mirrors backfill measure_tree pattern) — no scc required in CI.\n- [ ] Integration test (skipped if scc absent) over a small fixture tree.\n\n## Dependencies: Children 1, 2, 3\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/metrics/adapters/scc_loc.py (new), tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M (2 files)","id":"18f9-5b75-b909-408c","parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"LOC/size analyzer adapter via scc (deterministic shell-out, JSON parse)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784517464697193001,"uuid":"00fdf525-3243-44ae-91a4-9f949627bf45"}